						               													<description>A football (soccer) game which emphasizes the tactical aspect of the sport, with just enough luck involved to keep you thrilled.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Short rules summary:&amp;#10;The board is made up of circles resembling positions a footballist can take on the field. The circles are connected by lines which the footballists and the ball may travel along.&amp;#10;Each turn, both player rolls a die, and divides the result between his footballists. For each point a footballist may be moved to an adjacent circle. After that, the ball must be moved the same total amount of spaces. Unlike footballists, it can only change direction if it hits a freindly footballist. The ball's required movement may force the player to give the ball to the opposing team. &amp;#10;In addition to that, the ball goes to the opposing team anytime a 1 or 6 is rolled.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Has some similarities to Street Soccer, but predates that title by many years.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
